Vice President Mike Pence delivered remarks to the New York City Police Department (NYPD) expressing his admiration and gratitude for their service. He conveyed greetings from President Donald Trump and praised the NYPD for their dedication and courage in keeping the city and the nation safe. Pence also mentioned the absence of major terrorist attacks in the last 18 years and credited the NYPD, armed forces, and intelligence community for their efforts. He commended the NYPD on their recent football championship and acknowledged the sacrifices made by the officers and their families. Pence concluded by thanking the NYPD on behalf of the President and the American people.